  "sw_detailed": {
    "module_name": "EGTM_ATOM_3_Phase_Inverter_PWM",
    "public_functions": [
      {
        "signature": "void initEgtmAtom3phInv(void)",
        "behavior_description": "Initialize a 3-channel complementary, center-aligned PWM using the unified eGTM PWM driver with synchronous start/update and a period-event interrupt on the base channel. Algorithm and order: 1) Declare all config structures as locals: main Pwm config, per-channel config[3], per-channel dead-time config[3], one interruptConfig, and per-channel output pin config[3]. 2) Initialize the main config with defaults using the unified driver. 3) Build output[]: for each of the three logical channels, set pin and complementaryPin from the hardware-provided TOUT macros, set polarity high/complementary low, set push-pull mode, and set the specified pad driver. 4) Build dtmConfig[]: set deadTime.rising = 1e-6f and deadTime.falling = 1e-6f for each channel. 5) Build interruptConfig: mode=pulse-notify, isrProvider=cpu0, priority=20, vmId=0; assign periodEvent = IfxEgtm_periodEventFunction and dutyEvent = NULL. 6) Build channelConfig[0..2]: use logical timerCh indices Ch_0, Ch_1, Ch_2; set phase=0.0f; set duty to the initial percent values for the three phases; attach each channel’s dtm and output; mscOut=NULL; assign interrupt=&interruptConfig only on channelConfig[0]; set channelConfig[1].interrupt and channelConfig[2].interrupt to NULL. 7) Complete the main config: select the target cluster/submodule, set center alignment, enable syncStart and syncUpdate, set frequency to 20 kHz, set atom clock source to the first CMU clock (Clk_0), set DTM clock source accordingly, set numChannels=3, and point config.channels to channelConfig. 8) Enable-guard and CMU setup INSIDE the guard: if the eGTM is not enabled, enable it, then read the module frequency dynamically, configure the GCLK to run at that frequency by setting the divider to 1:1, configure CLK0 to derive from that frequency by programming the count appropriately, and enable the relevant clocks via the CMU clock-enable mask; all steps occur within the not-enabled branch. 9) Call the unified Pwm init with a persistent driver handle and a persistent channels array stored in this module’s state struct (the state holds the driver handle, channels array, dutyCycles[3], phases[3], deadTimes[3]). 10) After init, copy the initial duties and dead-time values from channelConfig/dtmConfig into the persistent state arrays for later use. 11) Configure the LED GPIO as a push-pull output using the port driver; do not set its level explicitly here (initial level control is not performed in the driver).",
        "driver_calls": [
          "IfxEgtm_Pwm_initConfig",
          "IfxEgtm_isEnabled",
          "IfxEgtm_enable",
          "IfxEgtm_Cmu_getModuleFrequency",
